(iStock) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Maiduguri - Police say a member of a civilian self-defense force has died while intercepting a suicide bomber at a mosque in northeastern Nigeria.Police spokesperson Victor Isukwu says the attack occurred early on Tuesday near the University of Maiduguri, where five people died in a bombing earlier this month.Isukwu says many others could have been killed if the self-defense member, a recent graduate of the university, had not intervened.Maiduguri is the birthplace of the Boko Haram insurgency.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.